Just to make clear, I hope that the silliness in my recent posts has not in any way come across as me making lite of the condition your nephews had that you did your best to spare your son from.  Not that you've accused me of such, you haven't, I Just wanted to make sure you knew that you have my sympathies for that, and what they went through is no laughing matter.  I've tried to keep the lighter comments seperated from our more serious discussions for that reason.<br>
<br>
Question for you before I concede that the only and best cure for the condition you described is only coincidentally also a powerful culturally ingrained tradition and that that was not at all related to the decision to circumcize:  Were steroid creams to loosen up the foreskin even discussed or tried?<br>
<br>
And if elasticity was of issue, wouldn't having even less skin, thus having to be stretched even farther, be even worse?<br>
